==Abstract==

This IIP describes package relay for transaction ancestors, enabling CPFP (Child Pays For Parent) across the P2P network. It is adapted from BIP 331 for INTcoin.

==Motivation==

A low-fee parent transaction may be rejected by mempools, preventing a high-fee child from being relayed. Package relay allows the child to "pay for" its parent by evaluating fees as a package.

==Specification==

===Messages===

'''sendpackages''': Signal package relay support
<pre>
version:    uint32
max_count:  uint32  // Max transactions per package
max_weight: uint32  // Max package weight
</pre>

'''getpkgtxns''': Request package transactions
<pre>
package_wtxids: []uint256
</pre>

'''pkgtxns''': Package transactions response
<pre>
txs: []CTransaction
</pre>

===Package Validation===

Packages are validated as a unit:
# All transactions must be valid individually (except fees)
# Package fee rate = (sum of fees) / (sum of weights)
# Package must meet minimum relay fee rate

===Package Topology===

Currently supported: child-with-unconfirmed-parents
* One child transaction
* One or more unconfirmed parent transactions
* Parents have no unconfirmed ancestors

===Fee Evaluation===

<pre>
package_feerate = sum(tx.fee for tx in package) / sum(tx.weight for tx in package)
</pre>

